BEGIN_PGML

Complete the following steps in order to find the curvature [`K`] of the curve
>>[` r(s) = ([$a]+s)i+j`],<<
where [`s`] is the arc length parameter.  

  
Step1: [` r'(s)=`][__________________________________________]{$ansrsderivative}  

Step2: [` ||r'(s)||=`][_______________________________________]{$ansrs}  

Step3: [`T(s)=\frac{r'(s)}{||r'(s)||}=`][_________________________________]{$ansrsderivative}  

Step4: [`T'(s)=`][________________________________________]{$ansZero} 

Final answer: [`K=||T'(s)||=`][__________________________]{$ansZero}  



